Preconditions:
The input array `arr` is not null.
The input array `arr` has at least three elements.
The input array `arr` is guaranteed to be a mountain, i.e., it has a peak.

Postconditions:
The returned index `i` is within the bounds of the input array `arr`.
The element at index `i` in the input array `arr` is greater than its adjacent elements.
The element at index `i` in the input array `arr` is the peak of the mountain.